## 2026-04-04 - No "Extract and Bind Unbound" fast-path in SelectionInspector
- Added "Extract X unbound" button to the SelectionInspector sync controls bar. When clicked, it sends `extract-tokens-from-selection` to the plugin, filters extracted tokens to only those with unbound properties (cross-referencing current `rootNodes` binding state), creates tokens via API with suggested names, and fires `apply-to-nodes` to bind them — all in one step with no review UI.
- Button only appears when `connected && activeSet && unboundWithValueCount > 0` (computed via `useMemo`). Shows "Extracting…" while in progress, success summary ("✓ Created N, bound N") or error inline after completion, each dismissible with ×.
- The existing "Extract" button (full panel) remains; the new button sits to its left and takes `ml-auto` to push the group right. The "Extract" button conditionally removes its own `ml-auto` when the fast-path element is visible.

