## 2026-04-04 - Plugin revert functions delete created variables/styles even when restores fail
- Added a guard in `revertVariables` (variableSync.ts) to skip the deletion phase when any restore `Promise.allSettled` result is rejected. The `restoresFailed` check wraps the entire deletion block (variables + collections) in an `else` branch.
- Added a guard in `revertStyles` (styleSync.ts) to skip the deletion phase when the `failures` array is non-empty after the restore loop. The delete loop is wrapped in an `else` branch.
- Both cases log a console.error explaining that deletions were skipped, so the partial rollback is visible in Figma DevTools.

